$
  (d Omega)/(d t) = -3/2 J_2 [R_E / (a(1-e^2))]^2 sqrt(mu / a^3) cos(i)
$

- $(d Omega)/(d t)$ - Nodal precession (rad/s)
- $J_2$ - Second zonal harmonic of the Earth's gravitational potential (unitless)
- $R_E$ - Earth's equatorial radius (km)
- $a=h+R_E$ - Semi-major axis of the orbit (km)
- $h$ - Altitude of the orbit perigree (km)
- $e$ - Eccentricity of the orbit (unitless)
- $mu$ - Standard gravitational parameter (km^3/s^2)
- $i$ - Inclination of the orbit (rad)



$
  i = cos^(-1){
    -2 / 3 (d Omega)/(d t) 1 / J_2 [
      a(1-e^2) / R_E
    ]^2 sqrt(a^3 / mu)
  }
$
